               <p>DAVID HYAMS. I am a <rs id="t18280911-261-viclabel1340" type="occupation">clothes-dealer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-261-victim1454 t18280911-261-viclabel1340"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18280911-261-crimeloc1341">Wardour-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-261-crimeloc1341" type="placeName" value="Wardour-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-261-crimeloc1341" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-261-off1338 t18280911-261-crimeloc1341"></join>. I was at my door on the 8th of August - I saw somebody put a hand in, and take a hat from my door; I did not see who it was, but I went out and saw the prisoner running - I called Stop thief! and my neighbour brought him back; the prisoner ran about thirty houses - I saw him stopped; I have not recovered the hat - there was another boy whom I saw.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-261-person1455">
                  WILLIAM 
                  RUFFLE
               <interp inst="t18280911-261-person1455" type="surname" value="RUFFLE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-261-person1455" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-261-person1455" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live with my father near the prosecutor's. On the 8th of August I saw the prisoner take the hat out and give it to his companion, who ran off; I did not see which way he ran, but I saw the prisoner run - I am sure he did not walk; I was looking out of window - I came running down to the door; I am sure the prisoner is the boy who took it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was walking up the street, and saw people running - I ran, and a man stopped me.</p>
               <p>
